    "• Some attack types can fall into both the offensive and adversarial AI categories, depending on their objectives and methods.",
    "For example, data poisoning attacks can be considered offensive AI when they are used to gain access or manipulate systems and data, but adversarial AI when their primary purpose is to deceive or exploit Fig. 3 A schema of adversarial AI attacks AI systems themselves.",
